Johannesburg Metro Police Department (JMPD) have on Saturday arrested two suspects in possession of a hijacked truck, containing jamming devices and Smart TVs worth R50 million.It is believed that the suspects were in the process of loading the TVs from one truck to another at the time of their arrest.According to reports the two suspect are expected to appear in court on charges related to hijacking and possession of stolen goods. The suspects used the jamming device to block the signal of the tracking company and the truck driver&#8217;s cellphone.&#8221;More to follow-TNA Reporter